==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Wall-sided
<hw>Wall"-sid`ed</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <fld>(Naut.)</fld>
<def>Having sides nearly perpendicular; -- said of certain vessels to
distinguish them from those having <xex>flaring</xex> sides, or sides
<xex>tumbling home</xex> (see under <er>Tumble</er>, <pos>v.
i.</pos>).</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Wall Street</ent>⟦br⟧
